name: CI
display_title: feat: add stderr logging for all 429 rate limit responses

head_commit.message:
feat: add stderr logging for all 429 rate limit responses

- Print to stderr when receiving 429 responses for visibility
- Log both during retry attempts and when max retries are exhausted
- Includes endpoint information and retry details in stderr messages
- Applied to all HTTP request methods:
  - Anonymous token acquisition
  - PDF session creation
  - Blank PDF session creation
  - General API requests

This ensures that rate limit events are always visible to users,
regardless of DEBUG mode, making it easier to diagnose and respond
to rate limiting issues.
